[{"category":"section","location":"api.html#API-reference","page":"API","text":"","title":"API reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api.html#Index","page":"API","text":"Modules = [NodeBasedModels]","title":"Index"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.BarnardClosure","page":"API","text":"BarnardClosure()\n\nImproved closure from Barnard et al. (2019) that conserves pairs. Uses a normalized correction ensuring Σ_A [ABC] = (n-1)[BC].\n\n[ABC] = (n-1) · ( (1-ϕ)·[AB][BC]/(n[B]) + ϕ·[AB][BC][CA] / ([A]·Σ_a [aB][aC]/[a]) )\n\nReference: Barnard et al. (2019), J. Math. Biol. 79:823–860\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.BarnardClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.BernoulliClosure","page":"API","text":"BernoulliClosure()\n\nOrdinary pair approximation (OPA). Assumes conditional independence of neighbor states. No clustering correction.\n\n[ABC] ≈ (n-1)/n · [AB][BC] / [B]\n\nReference: Rand (1999), Matsuda et al (1992)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.BernoulliClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.ClosureMethod","page":"API","text":"ClosureMethod\n\nAbstract type for triple closure approximations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.ClosureMethod"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.Compartment","page":"API","text":"Compartment(name; infectious=false)\n\nA disease compartment. Set infectious=true for compartments that can transmit infection (e.g., I in SIR).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.Compartment"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.CompartmentalModel","page":"API","text":"CompartmentalModel(compartments, transitions; name)\n\nA compartmental epidemic model. Defines the disease dynamics independently of network structure. The pairwise system is generated by combining this with a NetworkStructure and a ClosureMethod.\n\nExample\n\nsir = CompartmentalModel(\n    [Compartment(:S), Compartment(:I; infectious=true), Compartment(:R)],\n    [Transition(:S, :I, :τ, :infection),\n     Transition(:I, :R, :γ, :spontaneous)];\n    name = :SIR\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.CompartmentalModel"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.EamesClosure","page":"API","text":"EamesClosure()\n\nPlaceholder for Eames' hybrid closure for populations with regular (network) and random (mass-action) contacts.\n\n[ABC] ≈ (k_N-1)/k_N · [AB][BC]/[B] · ( (1-ϕ) + ϕ·[AC]·P/(k_N·[A][C]) )\n\nThe current package does not encode the additional regular/random-contact parameters required by the Eames model, so generate_pairwise rejects this closure instead of silently using a misleading surrogate.\n\nReference: Eames (2008), Theor. Popul. Biol. 73:104–111\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.EamesClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.GillespieResult","page":"API","text":"GillespieResult\n\nResult of an exact Gillespie (SSA) simulation of SIR on a graph.\n\nFields\n\nsol — JumpProcesses solution (piecewise-constant interpolation)\ngraph — the graph used\nN — number of nodes\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.GillespieResult"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.GillespieSISResult","page":"API","text":"GillespieSISResult\n\nResult of an exact Gillespie SIS simulation on a graph. Stores per-jump state snapshots so sol(t) can return the full N-vector at any time within [0, tmax]. Also stores infection_times[i] — the sorted list of times node i underwent an S→I event — so quantities like [S_p](t) and [I_p](t) (number of nodes with infection count p at time t) can be reconstructed for direct comparison with the reinfection-counting closure.\n\nFields\n\ntimes::Vector{Float64} — recorded event times (with times[1] = 0).\nstates::Vector{BitVector} — states[k][i] = true iff node i is  infectious in the interval [times[k], times[k+1]).\ngraph — the graph used.\nN::Int — number of nodes.\ninfection_times::Vector{Vector{Float64}} — per-node S→I event times.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.GillespieSISResult"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.GillespieSISResult-Tuple{Real}","page":"API","text":"(r::GillespieSISResult)(t::Real) -> BitVector\n\nPiecewise-constant interpolation: returns the state vector at time t.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.GillespieSISResult"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.GraphNetwork","page":"API","text":"GraphNetwork <: NetworkStructure\n\nNetwork defined by a specific graph instance. Used for individual-level, pair-based, and stochastic graph models.\n\nFields\n\ngraph — Graphs.jl AbstractGraph\ntransmission_matrix — matrix with T[i,j] equal to the per-edge infection rate from node j to node i, or nothing for a uniform infection rate supplied by the solver keyword arguments\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.GraphNetwork"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.HeterogeneousNetwork","page":"API","text":"HeterogeneousNetwork(degree_probs; ϕ=0.0, N=1.0)\n\nA heterogeneous network with degree distribution p_k for k = 0, 1, ..., K.\n\ndegree_probs — vector where degree_probs[k+1] = P(degree = k)\nϕ — global clustering coefficient\nN — total population size\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.HeterogeneousNetwork"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.HomogeneousNetwork","page":"API","text":"HomogeneousNetwork(n; ϕ=0.0, N=1.0)\n\nA homogeneous (regular) network where every node has degree n.\n\nn — degree of each node\nϕ — Keeling's clustering coefficient (ratio of triangles to triples)\nN — total population size (used for normalization)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.HomogeneousNetwork"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.IndividualBasedResult","page":"API","text":"IndividualBasedResult\n\nResult container for individual-based (order-1) model on a graph.\n\nFields\n\nsol — ODE solution\ngraph — the graph used\nN — number of nodes\nK — number of tracked states per node\nstate_names — names of tracked states (e.g., [:S, :I])\nmodel — original CompartmentalModel\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.IndividualBasedResult"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.KeelingClosure","page":"API","text":"KeelingClosure()\n\nKeeling's closure incorporating clustering coefficient ϕ. Extends the Bernoulli closure with a triangular correction term.\n\n[ABC] ≈ (n-1)/n · [AB][BC]/[B] · ( (1-ϕ) + ϕ · N·[AC]/(n·[A][C]) )\n\nReference: Keeling (1999), Morris (1997)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.KeelingClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.KirkwoodClosure","page":"API","text":"KirkwoodClosure()\n\nKirkwood superposition closure for triples on specific graphs. For a path k-i-j, uses conditional independence through the middle node i:\n\n⟨A_k B_i C_j⟩ ≈ [A_kB_i] × [B_iC_j] / ⟨B_i⟩\n\nThis is exact when there is no edge (k,j), i.e., on tree graphs. generate_pair_based uses this closure for graph-instance SIR models.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.KirkwoodClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.MotifClosure","page":"API","text":"MotifClosure(k, m)\n\nMotif/subgraph closure of order m on a k-regular host network class. Subtype of ClosureMethod. Currently only (k, m) = (2, 2) is implemented.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.MotifClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.MotifShape","page":"API","text":"MotifShape(n_nodes, edges, automorphisms, name)\n\nA connected induced-subgraph \"shape\": its vertex set, edge set, the automorphism group (each automorphism is a permutation of 1:n_nodes) and a symbolic name (e.g. :P2, :singleton).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.MotifShape"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.MotifSystem","page":"API","text":"MotifSystem\n\nContainer for a motif-closure ODE system.\n\nFields:\n\nshapes::Vector{MotifShape} — shape table (singleton + m-vertex shape(s))\nvariables::Vector{MotifVariable} — ordered list of dynamical variables\nindex::Dict{Tuple{Symbol,Vector{Symbol}},Int} — (shape.name, state) → index in variables\nrhs!::Function — closed-over (du, u, p, t) -> nothing\nu0::Vector{Float64} — initial condition (in variables order)\ntspan::Tuple{Float64,Float64}\nparams::NamedTuple — model parameters (e.g. (β=…, γ=…, k=…, N=…))\nmodel, network, closure — references to the underlying objects\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.MotifSystem"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.MotifVariable","page":"API","text":"MotifVariable(shape, state, orbit_size)\n\nA single dynamical variable: the count of induced subgraphs isomorphic to shape whose vertex states (in canonical order) are state. orbit_size is the size of the automorphism orbit of state (used for bookkeeping when converting to/from labeled quantities).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.MotifVariable"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.NeighbourhoodSystem","page":"API","text":"NeighbourhoodSystem\n\nContainer for an n=2 neighbourhood-closure ODE system on a k-regular host network.\n\nFields:\n\nk::Int — host degree.\nn::Int — neighbourhood order (currently always 2).\nvar_names::Vector{Symbol} — [:S_0, :S_1, …, :S_k, :I_0, :I_1, …, :I_k].\nindex::Dict{Tuple{Symbol,Int},Int} — (:S, y) → row index in u.\nrhs!::Function — (du, u, p, t) → nothing consuming p = (β, γ, k).\nu0::Vector{Float64} — initial condition.\ntspan::Tuple{Float64,Float64}\nparams::NamedTuple — (β, γ, k, N, ε).\nmodel, network — references to the underlying CompartmentalModel and NetworkStructure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.NeighbourhoodSystem"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.NetworkStructure","page":"API","text":"NetworkStructure\n\nAbstract type for network topologies used in pairwise models.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.NetworkStructure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.PairBasedResult","page":"API","text":"PairBasedResult\n\nResult container for pair-based (order-2) model on a graph.\n\nFields\n\nsol — ODE solution\ngraph — the graph used\nN — number of nodes\nn_directed_edges — number of directed edges (2 × undirected edges)\ndirected_edges — list of (i,j) pairs\nedge_index — Dict mapping (i,j) → edge index\nmodel — original CompartmentalModel\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.PairBasedResult"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.PairwiseSystem","page":"API","text":"PairwiseSystem\n\nContainer for the generated pairwise ODE system.\n\nFields:\n\nsystem — compiled ModelingToolkit system\nu0 — initial condition Dict\ntspan — time span\nparams — parameter Dict\nmodel — original CompartmentalModel\nnetwork — original NetworkStructure\nclosure — ClosureMethod used\nsingles — Dict of single variable symbols\npairs — Dict of pair variable symbols\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.PairwiseSystem"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.PowerClosure","page":"API","text":"PowerClosure(p)\n\nPower closure with exponent p. Interpolates between mean-field (p=1) and Bernoulli (p→∞).\n\n[ABC] ≈ (n-1)/n · [AB]^p · [BC]^p / [B]^(2p-1)\n\nReference: Rogers (2011)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.PowerClosure"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.Transition","page":"API","text":"Transition(from, to, rate, type)\n\nA transition between compartments.\n\ntype = :infection — rate is per-SI-edge transmission rate (τ)\ntype = :spontaneous — rate is per-capita rate (γ, σ, etc.)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.Transition"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels._compute_automorphisms-Tuple{Int64, Vector{Tuple{Int64, Int64}}}","page":"API","text":"_compute_automorphisms(n, edges) -> Vector{Vector{Int}}\n\nBrute-force automorphism group of the simple graph with vertex set 1:n and edge list edges. Iterates over all n! permutations and keeps those that preserve the (unordered) edge set. Used to build the 4-vertex shape constants below — for n = 4 this enumerates 24 permutations, which is trivial.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels._compute_automorphisms"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels._compute_p_min-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, Integer}","page":"API","text":"_compute_p_min(model, L) :: Dict{Symbol, Int}\n\nCompute the minimum reachable infection count for each base compartment. A compartment is p_min = 0 iff it is reachable from a susceptible without traversing any infection transition; otherwise p_min = min(1, L).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels._compute_p_min"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels._get_pair-Tuple{Dict, Symbol, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"Get pair variable, treating [AB] and [BA] as the same (undirected).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels._get_pair"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels._path_shape-Tuple{Int64}","page":"API","text":"_path_shape(m::Int) -> MotifShape\n\nReturn the path-graph shape on m vertices (P_m): vertices 1..m, edges {(i,i+1) : i=1..m-1}, automorphism group {identity, reflection}. For m ∈ {1, 2, 3} returns the corresponding pre-defined constant.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels._path_shape"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels._species_symbol-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"model_from_catalyst(rn::Catalyst.ReactionSystem; infectious=[:I])\n\nConvert a Catalyst ReactionSystem to a CompartmentalModel. Reactions with two reactants where one is in infectious are treated as infection transitions; all others are spontaneous.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels._species_symbol"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.aggregate-Tuple{GillespieResult, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"aggregate(r::GillespieResult, state; saveat=1.0)\n\nCount nodes in state over time. Returns (times, counts).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.aggregate"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.aggregate-Tuple{IndividualBasedResult, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"aggregate(result::IndividualBasedResult, state)\n\nAggregate a state across all nodes: X = Σi ⟨Xi⟩(t). Returns a vector over time points.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.aggregate"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.aggregate-Tuple{PairBasedResult, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"aggregate(result::PairBasedResult, state)\n\nAggregate a state across all nodes. Returns a vector over time points.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.aggregate"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.all_pairs-Tuple{CompartmentalModel}","page":"API","text":"Return all unique ordered pairs of compartment names.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.all_pairs"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.base_compartment_of-Tuple{Symbol}","page":"API","text":"base_compartment_of(name::Symbol) :: Symbol\n\nRecover the base compartment from a lifted name like :S_3 -> :S. Returns name itself when no _<digits> suffix is present.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.base_compartment_of"},{"category":"function","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.basic_reproduction_number","page":"API","text":"basic_reproduction_number(model, network, closure)\n\nCompute R₀ for a pairwise model. The method depends on the closure and network type.\n\nFor homogeneous SIR with Bernoulli closure:     R₀ = τ(n-2)/γ\n\nFor homogeneous SIR with Keeling closure (clustering ϕ):     R₀ depends on the fast-variable analysis at DFE\n\nFor heterogeneous networks (compact pairwise):     R₀_CPW = (a + √((2γ-a)² + 8γ(a+τ))) / (2γ)     where a = τ(⟨k²⟩ - 2⟨k⟩)/⟨k⟩ - γ\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.basic_reproduction_number"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.basic_reproduction_number-Tuple{NetworkStructure, ClosureMethod, Real, Real}","page":"API","text":"basic_reproduction_number(network, closure, τ, γ)\n\nCompute R₀ directly from network parameters and rates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.basic_reproduction_number"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.build_motif_symbolic_rhs-Tuple{MotifClosure}","page":"API","text":"build_motif_symbolic_rhs(closure::MotifClosure;\n                         model = :sis,\n                         closure_kind = :auto)\n    → (rhs!::Function, var_keys::Vector{Tuple{Symbol,Vector{Symbol}}},\n       params::NTuple{2,Symbolics.Num})\n\nIndependent Symbolics-based RHS oracle for the motif-closure SIS dynamics on a k-regular host. Returns a callable rhs!(du, u, p, t) (where p = (β, γ) is a 2-tuple/Vector of numeric values), the canonical variable-key list (matching the existing MotifSystem.variables order exactly), and the symbolic parameter pair (β_sym, γ_sym).\n\nThis builder enumerates motif shapes via enumerate_shapes and state classes via enumerate_state_classes, then assembles the symbolic dE/dt expressions from first principles using the closure registry described at the top of motif_symbolic.jl. It does NOT call any of the numeric _build_sis_k*_rhs builders; the resulting function is intended to be cross-checked against the numeric implementation as an oracle.\n\nCurrently model = :sis is the only supported model. Supported (closure.k, closure.m) pairs are those for which enumerate_shapes returns a non-error: k=2 with 2 ≤ m ≤ 6 and k=3 with m ∈ {2, 3}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.build_motif_symbolic_rhs"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.build_neighbourhood_symbolic_rhs-Tuple{Integer}","page":"API","text":"build_neighbourhood_symbolic_rhs(k::Integer)\n    -> (rhs_sym!, var_keys::Vector{Tuple{Symbol,Int}}, raw_exprs::Vector)\n\nIndependently build a symbolic RHS for the n = 2 neighbourhood-closure SIS dynamics on a k-regular network.\n\nReturns a tuple (rhs_sym!, var_keys, raw_exprs):\n\nrhs_sym!(du, u, p, t) — compiled function consuming a 2(k+1)-vector u in the canonical [S_0, …, S_k, I_0, …, I_k] order and a tuple p = (β, γ).\nvar_keys::Vector{Tuple{Symbol,Int}} — the same canonical ordering as (:S, 0), …, (:S, k), (:I, 0), …, (:I, k).\nraw_exprs::Vector{Num} — the symbolic RHS expressions in the same order (useful for inspection / debugging).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.build_neighbourhood_symbolic_rhs"},{"category":"function","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.build_pairwise","page":"API","text":"build_pairwise(args...; kwargs...)\n\nAlias for generate_pairwise. Provided for naming parity with EdgeBasedModels.jl's build_edge_system / build_sir family.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.build_pairwise"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.canonical_state-Tuple{MotifShape, AbstractVector{Symbol}}","page":"API","text":"canonical_state(shape, state) -> (canonical::Vector{Symbol}, orbit_size::Int)\n\nReturn the lexicographically-smallest representative of state under the shape's automorphism group, plus the orbit size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.canonical_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.compartment-Tuple{MotifSystem, Any, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"compartment(sys::MotifSystem, sol, base::Symbol) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nReturn the population-level trajectory of base state base (e.g. :S, :I). Aggregated from singleton variables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.compartment"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.compartment-Tuple{PairwiseSystem, Any, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"compartment(psys::PairwiseSystem, sol, state::Symbol)\n\nLook up the time series for the node-level compartment state (e.g. :S, :I) in the ModelingToolkit solution sol. Throws ArgumentError if state is not a known node-level compartment.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.compartment"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.default_initial_conditions-Tuple{PairwiseSystem}","page":"API","text":"default_initial_conditions(psys::PairwiseSystem)\n\nReturn the default initial conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.default_initial_conditions"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.degree_distribution_network-Tuple{AbstractVector}","page":"API","text":"degree_distribution_network(probs; ϕ=0.0, N=1.0)\n\nCreate a HeterogeneousNetwork from an explicit degree distribution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.degree_distribution_network"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.disease_free_equilibrium-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, NetworkStructure}","page":"API","text":"disease_free_equilibrium(model, network; N=1.0)\n\nCompute the disease-free equilibrium (DFE) for a pairwise system. At DFE: all nodes are susceptible, [S]=N, [SS]=nN, all other variables are zero.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.disease_free_equilibrium"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.early_growth_rate-Tuple{HomogeneousNetwork, BernoulliClosure, Real, Real}","page":"API","text":"early_growth_rate(network, closure, τ, γ)\n\nCompute the early exponential growth rate r₀ of the epidemic.\n\nFor homogeneous Bernoulli: r₀ = τ(n-2) - γ\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.early_growth_rate"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.enumerate_shapes-Tuple{MotifClosure}","page":"API","text":"enumerate_shapes(closure::MotifClosure) -> Vector{MotifShape}\n\nReturn the shape table for the requested (k, m). Phase B(a3) supports k = 2 and 2 ≤ m ≤ 6. The generic chain builder tracks only the singleton, the pair P_2, and the highest-order path P_m (intermediate P_j for 3 ≤ j < m are not stored — they are obtained on-the-fly as analytical marginals of P_m whenever needed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.enumerate_shapes"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.enumerate_state_classes-Tuple{MotifShape, AbstractVector{Symbol}}","page":"API","text":"enumerate_state_classes(shape, base_states) -> Vector{Tuple{Vector{Symbol},Int}}\n\nEnumerate all canonical state classes of shape over base_states, returned as (canonical_state, orbit_size) pairs in lex order.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.enumerate_state_classes"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.epidemic_threshold-Tuple{NetworkStructure, ClosureMethod, Real}","page":"API","text":"epidemic_threshold(model, network, closure)\n\nCompute the critical transmission rate τ_c above which an epidemic occurs.\n\nFor homogeneous Bernoulli: τc = γ/(n-2) For heterogeneous Bernoulli: τc = γ⟨k⟩/(⟨k²⟩ - ⟨k⟩)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.epidemic_threshold"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.erdos_renyi_network-Tuple{Real}","page":"API","text":"erdos_renyi_network(mean_degree; max_k=nothing, N=1.0)\n\nErdős–Rényi network with Poisson(meandegree) degree distribution. Truncated at `maxk` (default: meandegree + 5√meandegree).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.erdos_renyi_network"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.generate_individual_based-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"generate_individual_based(model, graph_net; kwargs...)\n\nGenerate and solve the order-1 (individual-based / NIMFA) ODE system on a specific graph. Uses pairwise independence: ⟨Si Ij⟩ = ⟨Si⟩⟨Ij⟩.\n\nThis is exact in the limit of infinite graph connectivity and provides an upper bound on the true epidemic. Errors arise from \"anomalous terms\" identified by Sharkey (2011) corresponding to 2-cycles.\n\nArguments\n\nmodel::CompartmentalModel — disease model (e.g., sir_model())\nnet::GraphNetwork — graph with transmission matrix\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ntspan — time span (default: (0.0, 100.0))\ninfection_rate — per-edge transmission rate τ (default: 0.5)\nrecovery_rate — recovery rate γ (default: 0.1)\ninitial_infected — vector of initially infected node indices (or nothing for random)\nε — backward-compatible alias for seed_fraction\nseed_fraction — fraction of random initial infected if initial_infected is nothing\nsaveat — time points to save solution (default: 1.0)\n\nReturns\n\nIndividualBasedResult containing the ODE solution and metadata.\n\nExample\n\nusing Graphs\ng = random_regular_graph(100, 6)\nnet = GraphNetwork(g)\nresult = generate_individual_based(sir_model(), net;\n    infection_rate=0.15, recovery_rate=0.1, initial_infected=[1,2,3])\nS_total = aggregate(result, :S)\n\nReferences\n\nSharkey (2011) \"Deterministic epidemic models on contact networks\" Eq. (30)\nVan Mieghem et al. (2009) \"Virus spread in networks\" (N-intertwined model)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.generate_individual_based"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.generate_neighbourhood-Tuple{Any, Integer, Integer}","page":"API","text":"generate_neighbourhood(model, k::Integer, n::Integer; β, γ,\n                       tspan=(0.0,100.0), N=1.0, ε=1e-3) -> NeighbourhoodSystem\n\nBuild a Keeling/House/Cooper/Pellis 2016 neighbourhood-closure SIS system on a k-regular host at neighbourhood order n.\n\nCurrently only n = 2 and SIS (sis_model()) are supported; other values throw ArgumentError.\n\nβ is the per-edge transmission rate (the paper's τ) and γ is the per-node recovery rate.  The initial condition is random mixing with infected fraction ε.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.generate_neighbourhood"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.generate_pair_based-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"generate_pair_based(model, net; kwargs...)\n\nGenerate and solve the order-2 (pair-based) ODE system on a specific graph. Uses Kirkwood triple closure: ⟨Ak Bi Cj⟩ ≈ [AkBi][BiCj]/⟨Bi⟩.\n\nCurrently supports the canonical SIR model on undirected graphs only. Exact on tree graphs; errors proportional to the density of 3-cycles (triangles).\n\nArguments\n\nmodel::CompartmentalModel — must be SIR\nnet::GraphNetwork — graph with transmission rates\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nclosure — triple closure method (must be KirkwoodClosure())\ntspan — time span (default: (0.0, 100.0))\ninfection_rate — per-edge transmission rate τ (default: 0.5)\nrecovery_rate — recovery rate γ (default: 0.1)\ninitial_infected — vector of initially infected node indices\nε — backward-compatible alias for seed_fraction\nseed_fraction — fraction of random initial infected if initial_infected is nothing\nsaveat — time points to save solution (default: 1.0)\n\nReturns\n\nPairBasedResult containing the ODE solution and metadata.\n\nVariable layout\n\nu[1:2N] — node variables: S1, I1, S2, I2, ..., SN, IN\nu[2N+1:2N+2M] — edge variables: SSe1, SIe1, SSe2, SIe2, ... where M is the number of directed edges.\n\nReferences\n\nSharkey (2011) Eq. (41): pair-based SIR on a graph\nKiss, Miller & Simon (2017) Ch. 5: pair-based models on networks\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.generate_pair_based"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.generate_pairwise-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, NetworkStructure, ClosureMethod}","page":"API","text":"generate_pairwise(model, network, closure; tspan=(0.0,100.0), N=1.0, ε=1e-3, seed_fraction=ε)\n\nGenerate a pairwise ODE system from a compartmental model, network structure, and triple closure approximation.\n\nReturns a PairwiseSystem containing the MTK ODESystem and initial conditions.\n\nClosure support matrix:\n\nClosure HomogeneousNetwork HeterogeneousNetwork\nBernoulliClosure ✓ ✓\nKeelingClosure ✓ ✓\nBarnardClosure ✓ ✗\nPowerClosure ✓ ✗\nEamesClosure ✗ ✗\n\nKirkwoodClosure is reserved for generate_pair_based on explicit graphs.\n\nExample\n\nsys = generate_pairwise(sir_model(), regular_network(6), KeelingClosure())\nsol = solve_pairwise(sys, Dict(:τ => 0.2, :γ => 0.1))\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.generate_pairwise"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sir-Tuple{GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"gillespie_sir(net; kwargs...)\n\nRun an exact Gillespie (SSA) SIR simulation on a specific graph using JumpProcesses.jl with the Direct aggregator.\n\nEach infected node can transmit to each susceptible neighbor at rate infection_rate. Each infected node recovers at rate recovery_rate.\n\nArguments\n\nnet::GraphNetwork — graph network\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ninfection_rate — per-edge transmission rate τ (default: 0.5)\nrecovery_rate — per-capita recovery rate γ (default: 0.1)\ninitial_infected — vector of initially infected node indices (default: [1])\ntmax — maximum simulation time (default: 100.0)\nseed — random seed (default: nothing)\n\nReturns\n\nGillespieResult with the full stochastic trajectory.\n\nExample\n\nusing Graphs\ng = random_regular_graph(100, 6)\nnet = GraphNetwork(g)\nresult = gillespie_sir(net; infection_rate=0.15, recovery_rate=0.1,\n                       initial_infected=[1,2,3])\nts, S_counts = aggregate(result, :S)\n\nReferences\n\nGillespie (1977) \"Exact stochastic simulation of coupled chemical reactions\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sir"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sir_average-Tuple{GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"gillespie_sir_average(net; nruns, kwargs...)\n\nRun multiple Gillespie simulations and compute time-averaged trajectories.\n\nReturns a NamedTuple with fields:\n\nt_grid — regular time grid\nS_mean, I_mean, R_mean — mean counts (Float64)\nS_q05, S_q95, I_q05, I_q95 — 5th/95th percentile bounds\nfinal_sizes — vector of final epidemic sizes from each run\n\nExample\n\navg = gillespie_sir_average(net; nruns=200, infection_rate=0.15,\n                            recovery_rate=0.1, initial_infected=[1])\n# avg.t_grid, avg.I_mean, avg.I_q05, avg.I_q95\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sir_average"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sis-Tuple{GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"gillespie_sis(net; kwargs...) -> GillespieSISResult\n\nExact Gillespie SSA for SIS on a graph. Each S–I edge fires infection at rate infection_rate; each I node recovers (back to S) at rate recovery_rate. Per-node S→I event times are recorded so reinfection counts can be reconstructed.\n\nnote: Migration path\nThis is the package's first-generation SSA, optimised for SIS only. For new code, prefer the companion package NetworkOutbreaks.jl which provides a general-purpose Direct-method SSA that works for any compartmental model (SIS, SIR, SEIR, …) and integrates with both NodeBasedModels.CompartmentalModel and EdgeBasedModels.DiseaseProgression. The integration testset \"NetworkOutbreaks integration\" in this package exercises that adapter; see also vignettes/15_reinfection_counting/index.qmd for a SIS reinfection-counting workflow that uses NetworkOutbreaks for ground-truth simulation. gillespie_sis will continue to be supported for back-compat, but no new features will be added.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ninfection_rate::Float64 — per-edge τ (default 0.5)\nrecovery_rate::Float64  — per-node γ (default 1.0)\ninitial_infected::Vector{Int} — initial I nodes (default [1])\ntmax::Float64 — simulation horizon (default 100.0)\nseed::Union{Int, Nothing} — RNG seed (default nothing)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sis"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sis_average-Tuple{GraphNetwork}","page":"API","text":"gillespie_sis_average(net; nruns, kwargs...)\n\nRun nruns independent Gillespie SIS simulations and return averaged prevalence trajectories. Returns a NamedTuple (t_grid, S_mean, I_mean, S_q05, S_q95, I_q05, I_q95).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.gillespie_sis_average"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.induced_subgraph_counts_4vertex-Tuple{Graphs.AbstractGraph}","page":"API","text":"induced_subgraph_counts_4vertex(g::AbstractGraph) -> NamedTuple\n\nBrute-force enumerate all 4-element vertex subsets of g and classify each induced subgraph by the number of internal edges and degree sequence. Returns a NamedTuple with fields (:p4, :k13, :paw, :c4, :k4me, :k4) containing the count of induced copies of each connected 4-vertex shape on a k-regular host (k = 3 is the typical use case but the helper makes no such assumption — it just classifies whatever 4-vertex induced subgraphs appear).\n\nTime complexity is O(N^4), fine for N ≲ 500.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.induced_subgraph_counts_4vertex"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.infection_count-Tuple{GillespieSISResult, Int64, Real}","page":"API","text":"infection_count(r::GillespieSISResult, i::Int, t::Real) -> Int\n\nNumber of S→I events node i has undergone by time t.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.infection_count"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.infection_count_of-Tuple{Symbol}","page":"API","text":"infection_count_of(name::Symbol) :: Union{Int, Nothing}\n\nRecover the infection count p from a lifted name. Returns nothing when the name is not in lifted form.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.infection_count_of"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.infection_transitions-Tuple{CompartmentalModel}","page":"API","text":"Return infection transitions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.infection_transitions"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.motif_based_sis-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"motif_based_sis(; β, γ, k, m,\n                 tspan=(0.0,100.0), N=1.0, ε=1e-3, kwargs...) -> MotifSystem\n\nBuild a motif-closure SIS system on a k-regular host with motif order m. Currently k = 2 with 2 ≤ m ≤ 6 is implemented:\n\nm = 2 (Phase B(a1)) and m = 3 (Phase B(a2)) use hand-derived specialised RHS builders.\nm ∈ {4, 5, 6} (Phase B(a3)) uses a generic chain builder that tracks only the singleton, the pair P_2, and the highest-order path P_m. Closure enters at the (m+1)-vertex level via the order-m Kirkwood/path factorisation:\nL_{(s_0, s_1, …, s_m)}_{P_{m+1}}\n    ≈ L_{(s_0, …, s_{m-1})}_{P_m} · L_{(s_1, …, s_m)}_{P_m}\n         / L_{(s_1, …, s_{m-1})}_{P_{m-1}}\nwhere L_{(σ)}_{P_{m-1}} is computed on-the-fly as a marginal of the tracked P_m variables.\n\nThe hidden kwarg _use_generic_chain_builder=false lets you A/B test the generic builder against the specialised m=3 builder. This is for diagnostic use only — the generic chain builder uses a strictly higher-order closure than the original m=3 builder, so the two RHSs agree exactly only at the random-mixing IC, not under perturbation.\n\nFor k = 3, m = 4, the system is implemented but should not be interpreted as a certified monotone refinement of m = 3: the Lean marginalisation theorems in EdgeBasedModels.jl/proofs/EBCMCategory/ show that the Kirkwood-form order-4 RHS need not project to a better order-3 RHS.\n\nOther (k, m) combinations throw ArgumentError.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.motif_based_sis"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.neighbourhood_compartment-Tuple{NeighbourhoodSystem, Any, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"neighbourhood_compartment(sys::NeighbourhoodSystem, sol, base::Symbol)\n    -> Vector{Float64}\n\nReturn the population-level trajectory of base state base (:S or :I) by summing over the neighbour-count axis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.neighbourhood_compartment"},{"category":"function","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.node_sir_model","page":"API","text":"node_sir_model(args...; kwargs...)\n\nDisambiguating alias for sir_model when used alongside EdgeBasedModels.jl. Returns a CompartmentalModel.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.node_sir_model"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.node_state-Tuple{GillespieResult, Int64, Float64}","page":"API","text":"node_state(r::GillespieResult, i, t)\n\nGet the state of node i at time t. Returns :S, :I, or :R.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.node_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.node_state-Tuple{IndividualBasedResult, Int64, Symbol, Int64}","page":"API","text":"node_state(result::IndividualBasedResult, i, state, t_idx)\n\nGet the probability that node i is in compartment state at time index t_idx.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.node_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.node_state-Tuple{PairBasedResult, Int64, Symbol, Int64}","page":"API","text":"node_state(result::PairBasedResult, i, state, t_idx)\n\nGet the probability that node i is in compartment state at time index t_idx.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.node_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.node_variables-Tuple{PairwiseSystem}","page":"API","text":"node_variables(psys::PairwiseSystem)\n\nReturn the Dict of node-level symbolic variables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.node_variables"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.pair_prob-Tuple{PairBasedResult, Int64, Int64, Symbol, Symbol, Int64}","page":"API","text":"pair_prob(result, i, j, a, b, t_idx)\n\nGet the probability P(node i in state a, node j in state b) at time index t_idx. Requires (i,j) to be a directed edge in the graph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.pair_prob"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.pair_variables-Tuple{PairwiseSystem}","page":"API","text":"pair_variables(psys::PairwiseSystem)\n\nReturn the Dict of pair-level symbolic variables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.pair_variables"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.population_fraction-Tuple{PairwiseSystem, Any, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"population_fraction(psys::PairwiseSystem, sol, state::Symbol; N=nothing)\n\nReturn the time series of the fractional population in compartment state. If the system was set up with single-totals summing to N (the default), pass N = sum_of_initial_singles to normalise; otherwise this returns the same value as compartment.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.population_fraction"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.regular_network-Tuple{Int64}","page":"API","text":"regular_network(n; ϕ=0.0, N=1.0)\n\nShorthand for HomogeneousNetwork(n; ϕ=ϕ, N=N).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.regular_network"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.reinfection_histogram-Tuple{GillespieSISResult, Real, Integer}","page":"API","text":"reinfection_histogram(r::GillespieSISResult, t::Real, L::Integer)\n\nCompute (S_counts, I_counts) where S_counts[p+1] is the number of nodes currently susceptible with infection-count min(p, L), and similarly for I_counts. p ranges from 0 to L.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.reinfection_histogram"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.reinfection_histogram_series-Tuple{GillespieSISResult, AbstractVector, Integer}","page":"API","text":"reinfection_histogram_series(r::GillespieSISResult, ts::AbstractVector,\n                              L::Integer) -> (S, I)\n\nCompute reinfection histograms over a time grid. Returns S::Matrix{Int} and I::Matrix{Int} of shape (L+1, length(ts)).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.reinfection_histogram_series"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.reinfection_totals-Tuple{PairwiseSystem, Any}","page":"API","text":"reinfection_totals(psys::PairwiseSystem, sol) :: Dict{Symbol, Vector{Float64}}\n\nAggregate the lifted node compartments back into base-compartment totals across the saved trajectory. Each value vector has length length(sol.t); the keys are the base compartment symbols.\n\nUseful for plotting: instead of plotting S_0, S_1, S_2, … separately, plot one curve for total S = Σ_p S_p.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.reinfection_totals"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.safe_ratio-Tuple{Real, Real}","page":"API","text":"safe_ratio(num, den; tol=1e-12) -> Float64\n\nNumerically safe ratio: returns 0.0 when den < tol, else num/den. The denominator is NOT clamped — the value is returned as-is when small, the ratio is simply set to zero. Used for closure terms of the form [AB][BC]/[B] that vanish when [B] does.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.safe_ratio"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.safe_ratio_sym-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API","text":"safe_ratio_sym(num, den) -> Num\n\nSymbolic counterpart of safe_ratio. Compiles to ifelse(den < 1e-12, 0, num/den) so it yields exactly zero (not NaN) when den underflows.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.safe_ratio_sym"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.seir_model-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"seir_model(; τ=:τ, σ=:σ, γ=:γ)\n\nSEIR model: S →[τ] E →[σ] I →[γ] R\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.seir_model"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.sir_model-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"sir_model(; τ=:τ, γ=:γ)\n\nStandard SIR model: S →[τ] I →[γ] R\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.sir_model"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.sirs_model-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"sirs_model(; τ=:τ, γ=:γ, ε=:ε)\n\nSIRS model: S →[τ] I →[γ] R →[ε] S (waning immunity)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.sirs_model"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.sis_model-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"sis_model(; τ=:τ, γ=:γ)\n\nSIS model: S →[τ] I →[γ] S (no immunity)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.sis_model"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.sis_state-Tuple{GillespieSISResult, Int64, Real}","page":"API","text":"sis_state(r::GillespieSISResult, i::Int, t::Real) -> Symbol\n\nReturn the state of node i at time t (:S or :I).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.sis_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.solve_motif-Tuple{MotifSystem}","page":"API","text":"solve_motif(sys::MotifSystem; saveat=nothing, alg=Tsit5(),\n            reltol=1e-8, abstol=1e-10, kwargs...)\n\nSolve the motif-closure ODE system. Returns the OrdinaryDiffEq solution object. Use compartment to extract per-compartment trajectories.\n\nDefault tolerances are tightened from OrdinaryDiffEq's defaults (reltol=1e-3, abstol=1e-6) to 1e-8/1e-10; closure ratios in the motif RHS amplify integration noise, so loose tolerances can let components drift negative. Pass reltol/abstol explicitly to override.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.solve_motif"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.solve_neighbourhood-Tuple{NeighbourhoodSystem}","page":"API","text":"solve_neighbourhood(sys::NeighbourhoodSystem; saveat=nothing,\n                    alg=Tsit5(), reltol=1e-8, abstol=1e-10, kwargs...)\n\nSolve the neighbourhood ODE.  Returns the OrdinaryDiffEq solution.\n\nDefault tolerances are tightened from OrdinaryDiffEq's defaults (reltol=1e-3, abstol=1e-6) to 1e-8/1e-10 for consistency with the other moment-closure solvers in this package; pass reltol/abstol explicitly to override.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.solve_neighbourhood"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.solve_pairwise-Tuple{PairwiseSystem, Dict}","page":"API","text":"solve_pairwise(psys::PairwiseSystem, params::Dict;\n               solver=nothing, reltol=1e-8, abstol=1e-10, kwargs...)\n\nSolve a PairwiseSystem with given parameter values.\n\nThe default tolerances (reltol=1e-8, abstol=1e-10) are tighter than OrdinaryDiffEq's defaults (1e-3, 1e-6). Looser tolerances are unsuitable for moment-closure systems with many tightly-coupled small components (e.g. reinfection-counting lifts at L≥2), where they can let components drift negative and the integrator report Unstable. Pass reltol/abstol explicitly to override.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.solve_pairwise"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.spontaneous_transitions-Tuple{CompartmentalModel}","page":"API","text":"Return spontaneous transitions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.spontaneous_transitions"},{"category":"function","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.triple_closure","page":"API","text":"triple_closure(A, B, C, pairs, singles, net, closure)\n\nCompute the symbolic expression for [ABC] given:\n\nA, B, C — compartment name symbols\npairs — Dict mapping (X,Y) => symbolic pair variable [XY]\nsingles — Dict mapping X => symbolic single variable [X]\nnet — NetworkStructure\nclosure — ClosureMethod\n\nReturns a Symbolics expression.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.triple_closure"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NodeBasedModels.with_reinfection_counting-Tuple{CompartmentalModel, Integer}","page":"API","text":"with_reinfection_counting(model::CompartmentalModel, L::Integer)\n\nReturn a lifted CompartmentalModel in which every base compartment X becomes a family of compartments X_p for p ∈ {p_min(X), …, L}, where p is the number of infections the node has experienced so far (capped at L).\n\nL::Integer ≥ 0 is the maximum tracked infection count. L = 0 is a no-op (returns a model isomorphic to model with names suffixed by _0). Choose L = 0 to recover the base pairwise dynamics.\nAn infection transition from → to lifts to from_p → to_{min(p+1, L)} for each reachable p.\nA spontaneous transition from → to lifts to from_p → to_p for each reachable p (when to's reachable set permits it).\nAll I_p (for any base infectious I) are marked infectious in the lifted model so the existing pair-equation generator picks them up as catalysts.\nParameter symbols are preserved, so a parameter dict that worked for the base model still works for the lifted model.\n\nReachability rule\n\nFor each base compartment X, the minimum reachable infection-count p_min(X) is 0 if X is reachable from a susceptible via only spontaneous transitions (susceptibles themselves, plus anything spontaneously reachable from a susceptible without ever being infected), otherwise min(1, L). This prunes the unphysical I_0 whenever L ≥ 1.\n\nExample (SIS with up to 4 infections tracked)\n\nbase   = sis_model()\nlifted = with_reinfection_counting(base, 4)\npsys   = generate_pairwise(lifted, regular_network(3; n_nodes = 1_000),\n                           BernoulliClosure(); tspan = (0.0, 80.0))\nsol    = solve_pairwise(psys, Dict(:τ => 0.5, :γ => 1.0))\ntotals = reinfection_totals(psys, sol)         # Dict(:S => …, :I => …)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NodeBasedModels.with_reinfection_counting"},{"category":"section","location":"vignettes.html#Vignettes","page":"Vignettes","text":"Worked examples for NodeBasedModels.jl. Source .qmd files live in vignettes/.\n\n01_sir_on_graphs — SIR Epidemic on a Graph\n02_network_effects — Effect of Network Topology\n03_moment_closure_hierarchy — The Moment Closure Hierarchy\n04_stochastic_validation — Stochastic Validation with Gillespie\n05_custom_models — Custom Compartmental Models\n06_population_vs_graph — Population-Level vs Graph-Instance Models\n07_pairwise_population_basics — SIR on a Network: Pair-Approximation Basics\n08_pairwise_r0_threshold — Basic Reproduction Number and Epidemic Threshold\n09_pairwise_clustering — Clustering Effects on Epidemic Dynamics\n10_reinfection_counting — Reinfection Counting for SIS on Networks\n11_motif_closures — Motif Closures and the Marginalisation Obstruction\n12_neighbourhood_model — Neighbourhood Models and the Ego-Network Closure\n13_combined_comparison — Combined comparison: four moment closures vs Gillespie\n14_motif_catalogue — Motif Shapes and State-Class Catalogue","title":"Vignettes"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#NodeBasedModels.jl","page":"Home","text":"Node-centric companion to EdgeBasedModels.jl for infectious-disease dynamics on networks. Where EBCMs track edge-level probabilities and a degree-distribution PGF, NodeBasedModels works at the level of individual nodes (and pairs of nodes), supporting:\n\nPopulation-level pairwise approximations — mean-field [X], [XY], [XYZ] ODEs on HomogeneousNetwork / HeterogeneousNetwork with a configurable triple closure.\nReinfection-counting pairwise lifts — SIS/SIRS-style infection-history towers X₀, …, X_L via with_reinfection_counting.\nMotif closures — connected induced-subgraph counts by shape and state class via motif_based_sis.\nNeighbourhood / effective-degree closures — ego-neighbourhood SIS states [S_y], [I_y] for n = 2 via generate_neighbourhood.\nGraph-instance approximations — order-1 individual-based and order-2 pair-based ODE systems on a specific Graphs.jl graph.\nStochastic Gillespie SIR/SIS simulators on arbitrary graphs.","title":"NodeBasedModels.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url = \"https://github.com/epirecipes/NodeBasedModels.jl\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Example","page":"Home","text":"using NodeBasedModels\n\nmodel   = sir_model()\nnetwork = regular_network(50; n_nodes = 5_000)\nclosure = KeelingClosure()\n\npsys = generate_pairwise(model, network, closure; tspan = (0.0, 80.0))\nsol  = solve_pairwise(psys, Dict(:τ => 0.05, :γ => 0.1))","title":"Example"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Documentation-contents","page":"Home","text":"Vignettes — worked examples covering pairwise closures, motif and neighbourhood approximations, and stochastic comparisons.\nAPI reference — exported types and functions.","title":"Documentation contents"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Companion-packages","page":"Home","text":"EdgeBasedModels.jl — edge-based compartmental models on configuration-model networks.\nNetworkOutbreaks.jl — stochastic simulation algorithms.","title":"Companion packages"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#License","page":"Home","text":"NodeBasedModels.jl is licensed under the MIT License.","title":"License"}]
